(286, 3, '2018-10-18 15:26:34', '2018-10-18 15:26:34', 'Fiduciary Trust Company International, a global wealth manager and wholly-owned subsidiary of Franklin Templeton Investments, has appointed David S. Bigelow IV as managing director and business development officer. Mr. Bigelow is based in New York and is responsible for building investment and trust relationships with individuals, families, and foundations in the Greater New York region.\r\n\r\n“During his career as a trusted advisor to families, entrepreneurs and philanthropic organizations, David has successfully drawn upon his relationships to cultivate new business,” said Emily Dreas, executive vice president and head of business development at Fiduciary Trust Company International. “We look forward to working with David as we continue to expand our New York office, and bring our comprehensive suite of investment and wealth management services to more clients throughout the surrounding area.” \r\n\r\nMr. Bigelow has more than 25 years of experience in the investment industry. He was most recently a senior banker and executive director at J.P. Morgan Private Bank, where he worked with wealthy individuals, owners of closely held businesses, and entrepreneurs. In this role, Mr. Bigelow provided trust and estate, credit, and advisory services to clients, and helped them identify strategies and investment solutions to achieve their long-term goals. Prior to joining J.P. Morgan, Mr. Bigelow was a senior consultant at NewOak Capital, an advisory firm, and served as product manager at Clinton Group, a hedge fund, where he built relationships with investors, rating agencies, monolines, and bankers. He also served as managing director of Radian Asset Assurance’s Financial Risk Solutions group. \r\n\r\nMr. Bigelow received his MBA in finance from The Wharton School at the University of Pennsylvania and his bachelor of arts in economics from Brown University. \r\n\r\nMr. Bigelow’s addition follows the recent appointments of Paulina Mejia as regional managing director, trust counsel, and head of Fiduciary Trust’s New York office, and Gerry Joyce as national head of the trust and estates. ', 'David Bigelow', 'Fiduciary Trust Company International, a global wealth manager and wholly-owned subsidiary of Franklin Templeton Investments, has appointed David S. Bigelow IV as managing director and business development officer. Mr. Bigelow is based in New York and is responsible for building investment and trust relationships with individuals, families, and foundations in the Greater New York region.', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'david-bigelow', '', '', '2018-10-19 16:57:57', '2018-10-19 16:57:57', '', 411, 'http://conference.siliconharlem.net/?post_type=speaker&#038;p=286', 302, 'speaker', '', 0),
(288, 0, '2018-10-24 01:42:37', '2018-10-24 01:42:37', 'Nina Nieuwoudt is the Vice President of Product Development and Innovation at Mastercard Labs. Nina heads the enterprise security portfolio, with a focus on driving identity and authentication solutions. Prior to joining Labs, Nina led the Mastercard New Consumers team to develop product and services targeting those at the base of the financial pyramid. Before relocating to the US, Nina was part of the business development team based in Johannesburg, South Africa. During that time, she launched the emblematic Government and Financial Inclusion SASSA (South African Social Security Agency) program which issued 10 million Mastercard-branded biometric cards, enabling the distribution of 17 million social grants monthly.', 'Nina Nieuwoudt', 'Nina Nieuwoudt is the Vice President of Product Development and Innovation at Mastercard Labs. Nina heads the enterprise security portfolio, with a focus on driving identity and authentication solutions. Prior to joining Labs, Nina led the Mastercard New Consumers team to develop product and services targeting those at the base of the financial pyramid.', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'nina-nieuwoudt', '', '', '2019-10-16 22:19:31', '2019-10-16 22:19:31', '', 410, 'http://conference.siliconharlem.net/?post_type=speaker&#038;p=288', 93, 'speaker', '', 0),
