(414, 1, '2019-08-05 05:42:22', '2019-08-05 05:42:22', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Silicon Harlem will hold this year’s 6<sup>th</sup> Annual Next Gen Tech Conference at the</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>National Black Theater on Friday, October 18<sup>th</sup>. This year’s conference theme is</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>“World 4.0: Let’s Get Ready!”&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>This year’s conference will build upon last year’s theme of the humanization of AI, Block Chain, Machine Learning, Driverless Cars, AR, VR and Smart Cities and extrapolate from there to provide the audience with an inclusive vision of the world as it undergoes profound change driven by the oncoming of the Fourth Industrial Revolution.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Our overarching questions that will propel us forward throughout the day are:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><li>How do I get a grasp on such profound material change?</li><li>What should I do to prepare to take advantage of these once-in-a-lifetime transformations?</li><li>What is being done both on the public institutional level and the level of the civic polity to ensure that we as citizens experience a positive transition into this new age?</li><li>From the standpoint of my family, how will this affect us from a multi-generational point-of-view?</li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Our objective is to make sure that Harlem, Upper Manhattan and it’s kindred communities both in and outside NYC are platformed so that they can leapfrog and take full advantage of the socio-economic opportunities that the next industrial revolution will create.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":740} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"http://siliconharlemconf:8886/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/4IR-white-01.svg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-740\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->', 'Agenda', 'Join us as we explore the vast  economic opportunities of the 4th Industrial Revolution.', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'agenda', '', '', '2019-08-20 20:24:27', '2019-08-20 20:24:27', '', 412, 'http://siliconharlemconf:8886/?page_id=414', 1, 'page', '', 0),
(415, 1, '2019-08-05 05:42:22', '2019-08-05 05:42:22', '', 'Agenda', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '414-revision-v1', '', '', '2019-08-05 05:42:22', '2019-08-05 05:42:22', '', 414, 'http://siliconharlemconf:8886/2019/08/05/414-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(416, 1, '2019-08-05 05:42:45', '2019-08-05 05:42:45', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>&nbsp;We\'re expecting a capacity crowd for this year\'s event. Make sure to get your registration early before they sell out!</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\nSilicon Harlem is in full production of our 6th Annual Next0Gen Tech Conference, taking place on Friday, October 18, 2019. The theme is “World 4.0 - Let’s Get Ready!”. This year we are thrilled about advanced technology subjects that include Extended Reality, Next Gen Education, Volumetric Video, Artificial Intelligence, Robotics, Quantum Computing, Tech Enabled Communities and so much more. These new trends are defining the 4th Industrial Revolution and your voice must be at the table.\n\nIf you are not sure about attending, here are the top 5 reasons to be there:\nThe networking is extraordinary. The conference is the perfect place to make contacts. Meet investors, collaborators or simply increase your personal or company brand, to a robust talented diverse audience.\n\nSee the future. The conference is designed to prepare attendees for technology advancements that will impact all industries moving forward. Learn about new things!\n\nBe a geek for a day. The focus on new technology will blow your mind. Our expert speakers will walk us through the good and the challenge of our world.\nInternationalize your brand. The conference features an all day pitch competition between Rwanda and Harlem. This conference is worldwide!\n\nIf you’re an agency/nonprofit, or private company looking to add dynamic talent, you can find your match at the Silicon Harlem Conference Job Fair and MWBE information. Look for the MeetUp Space to connect at the epicenter of opportunity.\n\nPlease note: the registration fee for the Silicon Harlem Next Gen Tech Conference 2019 at the National Black Theatre, 2031 5th Ave, New York, NY 10035, is $150 which includes the Charles B. Rangel Awards Luncheon.  Students, academic, government, and nonprofit rates are available.\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'Why Attend', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'registration', '', '', '2019-10-11 19:31:47', '2019-10-11 19:31:47', '', 412, 'http://siliconharlemconf:8886/?page_id=416', 2, 'page', '', 0),
