(702, 0, '2019-08-13 09:33:35', '2019-08-13 09:33:35', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Part One of our featured panels will discuss “Life in the City of the Future” What will the conduct of daily life look like in the imminent age of automation? Join us for an interactive discussion where we will co-envision a city where all people especially those who have historically been the least advantaged are enabled to reap the benefits of autonomous vehicles, on-demand services and ubiquitous AI.<br></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'World 4.0 - Let\'s Get Ready', 'Our panel of visionaries will discuss urban living in the 4th Industrial Revolution Era. What skills are going to matter? What choices will we have and which will be made for us? We’ll be discussing the catalysts evolving telecommuting and transportation, social and civic interaction, health and education in the years ahead to help you get ready for the economic opportunities of the future.', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'feature-panel-nyc-2050-lets-get-ready', '', '', '2019-10-07 15:35:13', '2019-10-07 15:35:13', '', 697, 'http://siliconharlemconf:8886/?post_type=session&#038;p=702', 17, 'session', '', 0),
(703, 0, '2019-08-13 09:39:35', '2019-08-13 09:39:35', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>DARQ stands for “Distributed Ledger Technologies (Blockchain), Artificial intelligence, Extended Reality and Quantum Computing. These four transformative technologies are expected to have an explosive impact on society. Our panel will tackle these expanding interrelated technologies to build a more equitable future in the global technology job market and how these technologies can be leveraged to benefit humanity.<br></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'DARQ Matters - DLT, AI, XR, Quantum', 'Blockchain, Artificial intelligence, XR (Virtual/Augmented/Mixed Reality), and Quantum Computing are expected to have explosive enterprise growth in the next few years, but what impact will they have on society and communities?\nOur panel of top experts from each of these four realms of technologies will tackle expanding representation in these interrelated fields to build a more equitable future in the global technology job market and how these technologies can be purposed to benefit humanity.\n', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', '1a-darq-matters-blockchain-ai-xr-quantum', '', '', '2019-10-11 20:20:50', '2019-10-11 20:20:50', '', 697, 'http://siliconharlemconf:8886/?post_type=session&#038;p=703', 22, 'session', '', 0),
(706, 0, '2019-08-13 10:08:47', '2019-08-13 10:08:47', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>This new wave of innovation driven by automation and digitalization creates the opportunity for Africa to leapfrog into the fourth industrial revolution accelerating development and harnessing the full capability of its resources. More than half of global population growth between now and 2050 will occur in Africa. With a median age of 18, Africa boasts the youngest population in the world . This panel will explore partnership opportunities to collaborate and share knowledge to propel Africa forward.<br></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'Harnessing the Global Potential', 'Our virtual personal assistants and our always on smart phones have changed how we navigate everyday activity. The goal is to create opportunities for more efficient living. Tech-enabled communities and cities have embraced urban data as a means to improve efficiency for people by getting data from calls into government agencies, statistics on public transportation, air quality and energy production. Does this dependency on technology and data lead to harmony for all or will it push citizens further into isolation.\n', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'the-world-is-technology-dependent', '', '', '2019-10-09 19:43:46', '2019-10-09 19:43:46', '', 697, 'http://siliconharlemconf:8886/?post_type=session&#038;p=706', 23, 'session', '', 0),
(707, 0, '2019-08-13 10:10:37', '2019-08-13 10:10:37', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The Charles B. Rangel Award Luncheon is a great highlight of the conference. It is an opportunity to recognize the efforts of so many and foster new relationships in the tech sector. Do not miss it this year as we recognize an innovative individual we can all celebrate. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'Rangel Award Luncheon', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'rangel-award-luncheon', '', '', '2019-10-16 21:28:44', '2019-10-16 21:28:44', '', 697, 'http://siliconharlemconf:8886/?post_type=session&#038;p=707', 24, 'session', '', 0),
(710, 0, '2019-08-13 10:50:14', '2019-08-13 10:50:14', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Volumetric Content is the next major evolution in media.<br></strong>It captures real depth which is rendered as holograms in Light-field displays and Virtual, Augmented, and Mixed Reality headsets. The Spatial Computing technology used to create video games and special effects for movies allows Six Degrees of Freedom to move within and around virtual environments and objects, where you get to be the camera. This is industry-changing as a collaborative platform; with wide-ranging enterprise use-cases in education, health, manufacturing, travel, architecture, and real estate as well as journalism, sports, gaming and entertainment for consumers. This panel will explore how the multi-billion dollar XR space will create unprecedented opportunity using the full stack of World 4.0 technologies.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'Spatial Computing and the Future of Content', 'The technology that makes special effects for movies are making possible the holograms the movies inspired. Today’s Virtual Reality and Mixed Reality content made by gaming engines create holograms that we can move within and around with Six Degrees of Freedom. Volumetric video capture measures real depth and requires massive computing resources that use all the technologies of the 4th Industrial Revolution. This isn’t our grandchildren’s 3D, it’s our grandchildren’s. ', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'spatial-computing-and-the-future-of-content', '', '', '2019-10-09 19:43:00', '2019-10-09 19:43:00', '', 697, 'http://siliconharlemconf:8886/?post_type=session&#038;p=710', 26, 'session', '', 0),
(711, 0, '2019-08-13 11:09:20', '2019-08-13 11:09:20', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The keys to unlocking the economic opportunities of the 4th Industrial revolution is educational opportunities. As we continued using analog learning methods deep into the digital age, in the virtual age, those old rules no longer need apply. New technology allows us to completely re-examine pedagogy itself, along the roles of teachers and mentors as guides. This panel will explore how personalizing education to an individuals strengths and ability is now possible at scale.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'Reimagining Education', 'From privacy violations, to election tampering to deep fakes, the public confidence in data is shattered. How do we grow out of our technological adolescence and use our connectivity to build a future we want?', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'restoring-faith-in-social-media-and-civic-institution', '', '', '2019-10-16 21:48:07', '2019-10-16 21:48:07', '', 697, 'http://siliconharlemconf:8886/?post_type=session&#038;p=711', 29, 'session', '', 0),
(712, 0, '2019-08-13 11:10:47', '2019-08-13 11:10:47', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Cybercrime can be devastating for small business. Identity theft, malware, phishing scams, ransomware attacks can cripple a business causing disruption to daily operations, impacting ability to conduct business and have serious economic consequences. New York City is tackling these threats head-on with collaboration across government and the business. We’ll hear from the people and agencies leading these efforts, gain insight into the impact of cyber threats on business and discuss the resources available to help bolster resilience and mitigate attacks.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'Tackling Cyber Threats |  Public/Private Collaboration', 'Global Interconnectivity is driven by technology and innovation as we usher in the 4th industrial revolution. Our panel of experts will discuss how international business and the public sector, will transition to augmentation, virtual services, dynamic markets, and convergence, that the 4th industrial revolution represents\n', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'techs-impact-on-globalization', '', '', '2019-10-11 14:36:21', '2019-10-11 14:36:21', '', 697, 'http://siliconharlemconf:8886/?post_type=session&#038;p=712', 27, 'session', '', 0),
(713, 0, '2019-08-13 11:21:59', '2019-08-13 11:21:59', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nThe role of\ncreativity in STEM and the impact it will have on the technology of the future.\n\n\n\n</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'Keynote: STEM Creativity and the future of Technology', 'The role of creativity in STEM and the impact it will have on the technology of the future.', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'afternoon-keynote', '', '', '2019-10-11 13:41:27', '2019-10-11 13:41:27', '', 697, 'http://siliconharlemconf:8886/?post_type=session&#038;p=713', 32, 'session', '', 0),
(714, 0, '2019-08-13 11:26:34', '2019-08-13 11:26:34', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>This international pitchfest will feature 3 startup companies from NYC and 3 startups from Rwanda.  Three separate will feature pairs of one NY and One Rwandan startup. Winners will be announced following the Afternoon Keynote.<br><br></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'Harlem to Rwanda!', 'The rollout of gigabit-capacity low-latency wireless networks is enabling billions of devices to come online over the coming years, promising another rapid evolution of how society functions. Then we’ll tackle the science around some of the many questions the community has about this and give you the tools to understand the next generation of connectivity and devices.', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', '3b-5g-edge-networks-and-the-internet-of-everything', '', '', '2019-10-08 19:51:26', '2019-10-08 19:51:26', '', 0, 'http://siliconharlemconf:8886/?post_type=session&#038;p=714', 19, 'session', '', 0),
(715, 0, '2019-08-13 11:30:15', '2019-08-13 11:30:15', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><em>Part Two of our featured panels explores the opportunities created by global interdependence and life in the tech-enabled cities of the future.&nbsp; We have already seen deployments of AI and Computer Vision on mass scale, self driving cars, robots and automation, what does it mean for the generation being raised and the generation aging into this brave new world.</em><br></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'WORLD 4.0 - Let’s Lead the Way!', 'Part Two of our featured panels explores the opportunities created by global interdependence and life in the tech-enabled cities of the future.  We have already seen deployments of AI and Computer Vision on mass scale, self driving cars, robots and automation, what does it mean for the generation being raised and the generation aging into this brave new world.', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'world-4-0-lets-lead-the-way', '', '', '2019-10-11 14:39:00', '2019-10-11 14:39:00', '', 697, 'http://siliconharlemconf:8886/?post_type=session&#038;p=715', 36, 'session', '', 0),
(716, 0, '2019-08-13 11:32:24', '2019-08-13 11:32:24', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Our Silicon Harlem Town Hall is an opportunity for you to share and discuss a variety of topics around community growth and sustainability. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The town hall is an open forum without any specific rules other than being respectful and concise. It is our hope that ideas shared can be turned into goals we can collectively embrace and organize to achieve. Your voice is critical!</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'Town Hall - Open Forum', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'town-hall-open-forum', '', '', '2019-10-11 14:39:54', '2019-10-11 14:39:54', '', 697, 'http://siliconharlemconf:8886/?post_type=session&#038;p=716', 37, 'session', '', 0),
