(742, 0, '2019-08-18 23:18:51', '2019-08-18 23:18:51', 'Ben Erwin is the Executive Director of the fifth and sixth editions of the Silicon Harlem Annual Next-Gen Tech Conferences. With over 25 years in technology, as a full-stack web developer and data scientist Ben has worked on numerous campaigns for major agencies including The New York Times’ T-Brand Studio, Likeable Media, and has been working with Clayton Banks since 2004 when he served as VP and General Manager of Ember Media. Ben consulted for the United Nations for 14 years as webmaster for Special Representatives of Office of the Secretary-General. He is an avid photographer, autodidact, digital polymath, early adopter and internet frontiersman. Ben is an expert and researcher on the integration of emerging technologies and is currently writing a White Paper on Volumetric Content and Volumetric Displays aka Holograms.', 'Ben Erwin', 'Ben Erwin is the Executive Director of the fifth and sixth editions of the Silicon Harlem Annual Next-Gen Tech Conferences. With over 25 years in technology, as a full-stack web developer and data scientist Ben has worked on numerous campaigns for major agencies including The New York Times’ T-Brand Studio, Likeable Media, and Ember Media. Ben is an expert and researcher on the integration of emerging technologies and is currently writing a White Paper on Volumetric Content and Volumetric Displays aka Holograms. ', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'ben-erwin', '', '', '2019-10-16 21:35:42', '2019-10-16 21:35:42', '', 410, 'http://siliconharlemconf:8886/?post_type=speaker&#038;p=742', 145, 'speaker', '', 0),
