(791, 1, '2019-09-23 00:32:51', '2019-09-23 00:32:51', '<p>Silicon Harlem is proud and delighted to be back hosting our 6th Annual Conference at the historical National Black Theatre during their 50th anniversary jubilee year. NBT was founded in 1968 by actress, director, producer, Dr. <a title=\"Barbara Ann Teer\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Barbara_Ann_Teer\">Barbara Ann Teer</a>.&nbsp;Teer purchased the 8,000 square foot theatre in 1969 at 9 East 125th street. In 1982, the NBT expanded to 64,000 square foot complex that houses two theatres, classrooms, and an African and Nigerian art gallery which resides on 5th Avenue at 125th Street in Harlem, and will be closing 2019 for redevelopment. Stay tuned for the announcement of where the 2019 Conference will be held.</p>\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'Venue', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '9-revision-v1', '', '', '2019-09-23 00:32:51', '2019-09-23 00:32:51', '', 9, 'http://siliconharlemconf.192.168.1.11.xip.io:8886/2019/09/23/9-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
