(840, 0, '2019-09-27 17:44:56', '2019-09-27 17:44:56', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Debra is currently Founder &amp; CEO at LEVER3, a Digital Studio start up based in Brooklyn, NY.&nbsp; Here, her focus is on design and development of software tools for AR/VR/XR. She has worked professionally in the media production and technology industries for over 15 years.&nbsp; </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Debra Co-Founded and launched The Lightframe Co.- a volumetric mixed reality capture studio producing holograms. Also, she lead Sales for the Eastern Region US for X2O Media, a digital communications platform and worked several other international technology companies in leadership roles; Tandberg, Cisco and Barco.&nbsp; </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>With a legacy background in storytelling, a business leader and enthusiast, speaker, and a keen understanding of the role technology has in developing and delivering immersive content engagements, she joins us with a multidisciplinary approach.&nbsp; Debra received her B.A. in Film Studies from the University of California – Berkeley. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'Debra Simmons', 'Debra is currently Founder & CEO at LEVER3, a Digital Studio start up based in Brooklyn, NY.  Here, her focus is on design and development of software tools for AR/VR/XR. She has worked professionally in the media production and technology industries for over 15 years.  Prior Debra Co-Founded and launched The Lightframe Co.- a volumetric mixed reality capture studio producing holograms.', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'debra-simmons', '', '', '2019-10-17 13:48:12', '2019-10-17 13:48:12', '', 410, 'http://siliconharlemconf.192.168.1.11.xip.io:8886/?post_type=speaker&#038;p=840', 92, 'speaker', '', 0),
