(876, 0, '2019-10-02 16:29:15', '2019-10-02 16:29:15', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Donald is an Executive Director in the CCB Business Modeling Team focusing on Machine Learning and Artificial Intelligence.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>He joined JPMC from Moody’s Analytics, where he was a Senior Director in their Content Solutions department. In that role, he was Head of Operations Research and responsible for complex projects involving applied mathematics, operations research, data science, machine learning, quantitative finance and software development. Prior to that, he was Vice President and Head of Research Technology Implementation for Moody’s Research Labs. Donald also worked in several research groups as a senior quantitative developer during his 16-year tenure with Moody’s Corporation.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>In addition to Moody’s, Donald worked at Morgan Stanley in the Securitized Products Group of their Fixed-Income division. There, he worked with U.S. private-label residential mortgage-backed securities and he developed real-time trading and interest rate risk analysis applications.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Donald holds a master’s in mathematics from St. John’s University; a bachelor’s in computer science from Sacred Heart University; a graduate degree in quantitative methods from Columbia University; and a graduate degree in artificial intelligence from Stanford University.<br></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'Donald Stephens', 'Donald is an Executive Director in the CCB Business Modeling Team focusing on Machine Learning and Artificial Intelligence.', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'donald-stephens', '', '', '2019-10-16 21:14:13', '2019-10-16 21:14:13', '', 410, 'https://conference.siliconharlem.com/?post_type=speaker&#038;p=876', 256, 'speaker', '', 0),
