(925, 0, '2019-10-08 21:00:52', '2019-10-08 21:00:52', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>\n\nJanet Haven is the Executive Director of Data &amp; Society. Previously, she served Data &amp; Society as Director of Programs and Strategy. Prior to Data &amp; Society, Haven worked for more than a decade at the Open Society Foundations, where she oversaw funding strategies and grant-making related to technology’s role in supporting and advancing civil society, particularly in the areas of human rights and governance/accountability. Haven started her career in technology start-ups in Central Europe, participating in several successful acquisitions. She sits on the board of the Public Lab for Open Science and Technology and advises a range of non-profit organizations. Haven holds an MA from the University of Virginia, and a BA from Amherst College.\n\n</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'Janet Haven', ' Janet Haven is the Executive Director of Data & Society. Previously, she served Data & Society as Director of Programs and Strategy. Prior to Data & Society, Haven worked for more than a decade at the Open Society Foundations, where she oversaw funding strategies and grant-making related to technology’s role in supporting and advancing civil society, particularly in the areas of human rights and governance/accountability. Haven started her career in technology start-ups in Central Europe, participating in several successful acquisitions. She sits on the board of the Public Lab for Open Science and Technology and advises a range of non-profit organizations. Haven holds an MA from the University of Virginia, and a BA from Amherst College. ', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'janet-haven', '', '', '2019-10-16 21:47:07', '2019-10-16 21:47:07', '', 410, 'https://conference.siliconharlem.com/?post_type=speaker&#038;p=925', 279, 'speaker', '', 0),
